<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDMONDS' REHAB IS NEARLY COMPLETE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Jim Edmonds left his temporary teammates at
Single-A Lake Elsinore and rejoined his Anaheim Angels teammates
Friday, if only for a day.
</P>
<P>
   Edmonds took batting practice in front of Terry Collins to show
his manager his surgically repaired right shoulder is fine. Edmonds
will go back to play for Lake Elsinore tonight at San Bernardino,
then is expected to join the Angels' roster Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   After going 0 for 4 in his first game for the Storm on Monday,
Edmonds went 6 for 11 in his next three games.
</P>
<P>
   ``I called Terry and told him I'm ready,'' Edmonds said. ``He
said to play in one more game (tonight) and see how it goes. It's
felt really good, better than I thought it would.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted to see him hit today,'' Collins said. ``He's much
better than when we left (on the last road trip).''
</P>
<P>
   Though he'll probably be back Sunday, Edmonds probably won't be
in center field for about two weeks. Instead, he'll be the DH.
</P>
<P>
   ``I made a deal with the doctor,'' Edmonds said. ``I could come
back if I don't play the outfield.''
</P>
<P>
   The Angels medical staff is more concerned about Edmonds
reinjuring the shoulder playing defense, where he might dive for a
ball or run into a wall.
</P>
<P>
   Greene returns: Replacing Randy Velarde and Omar Olivares _
traded Thursday to the A's _ on the roster were Andy Sheets and
Todd Greene. Greene had been sent to the minors to work on a swing
that has been out of whack, and he hit .243 with five homers and 14
RBI in 19 games while at Triple-A Edmonton.
</P>
<P>
   Sheets is expected to make some starts at second, but Jeff Huson
started Friday's game.
</P>
<P>
   Also: Pitcher Mike James, out all season recovering from
reconstructive elbow surgery, will begin a rehab assignment at Lake
Elsinore today. James could be activated in about a week....
Pitcher Tim Belcher (broken right pinky finger) will throw his
second simulated game today and is expected to return to the
starting rotation by next weekend.... Outfielder Matt Luke,
recovering from a strained muscle in his side, injured his wrist
swinging at Lake Elsinore. There is no timetable for his return.
</P>
</TEXT>
