<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Aug. 1 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   GANGS-LURE (Los Angeles) _ With few places for children to go
after school, police and parents alike say gangs are an easy choice
for youngsters. By Jesse Hiestand and Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move
in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   EXOTIC-ANIMALS (Los Angeles) _ With Hollywood in its back yard
and relatively wide open spaces for Los Angeles, the San Fernando
Valley is home to nearly half of the city's licensed exotic
animals. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   TEST-TECHNIQUES (Los Angeles) _ The San Fernando Valley
elementary schools that fared best in this year's round of Stanford
9 tests have several things in common, including prepping students
on test-taking techniques. Some critics warn that learning to take
tests could come at the expense of learning the material, an
allegation school officials deny. By David Baker. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
