<HEADLINE>
O.D.B., NEW YORK RAP ARTIST, CHARGED WITH DRUG POSSESSION 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ The Brooklyn rapper known as O.D.B. was arrested
Saturday after police stopped him for running a red light and found
what they believed to be crack cocaine and a bag of marijuana in
his 1994 Mercedes-Benz convertible, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   The rapper, whose real name is Russell P. Jones, 30, was stopped
in Queens and could not produce a driver's license, registration or
other proof of ownership of the car, said Sgt. Brian Burke, a
police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Burke said the officers arrested Jones for driving without a
license, and during a search of his vehicle found what they
believed to be a bag of marijuana and 20 bags of crack cocaine.
</P>
<P>
   Jones was charged with criminal possession of a controlled
substance and driving on a suspended license. Jones is a member of
the Wu-Tang Clan, the Staten Island rap group that he helped start
seven years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-31-99 1615EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990731.0169 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 16:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
