<HEADLINE>
KINGS SIGN TSYPLAKOV
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Restricted free agent left wing Vladimir Tsyplakov, whose
disappointing performance last season symbolized the frustrations
of the Kings, signed a one-year contract with the team Saturday
worth about $600,000.
</P>
<P>
   Tsyplakov, 30, had only 11 goals and 23 points last season,
which placed him seventh on the offensively-challenged Kings. His
output represented a 29-point drop-off from his career-high
18-goal, 34-assist performance in 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
   Tsyplakov missed 12 games last season with a sprained left knee.
The Kings begin training camp at Iceoplex in five weeks. The season
begins Oct. 2 in Nashville.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-31-99 2112EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
