<SLUG> BC-WOODSTOCK-SEXATTACK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN ACCUSED OF SEX ATTACK AT WOODSTOCK  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A New York prison guard has been charged with sexually
assaulting a 15-year-old who had left the rampaging crowds at
Woodstock '99 last weekend to find a bathroom, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The arrest is the first for a sex crime related to the concert,
but local prosecutors and the State Police are investigating
several other reported sexual assaults.
</P>
<P>
   The guard, Timothy A. Weeden, 26, of Rome, N.Y., demanded oral
sex from the woman, said Richard D. Dodge, an investigator for the
Oneida County Child Advocacy Center.
</P>
<P>
   The woman stopped in Rome at a convenience store about a mile
from the concert at about 2:30 a.m. Monday, officials said. The
restroom was out of order, so she walked behind the building,
officials said. Weeden approached her and said she could be charged
with indecent exposure, the investigator said. He led her behind
some trees and attacked her, Dodge said.
</P>
<P>
   Weeden has been suspended from his job at a state prison in
Marcy. He was indicted Tuesday on charges of first-degree sodomy,
third-degree sodomy, first-degree sexual abuse and endangering the
welfare of a child, Dodge said.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
